<h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline">NYC Medical Workers Protest New Policy Demanding Doctor’s Notes for Ill Staffers</h1>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<div class="row featured-media-block"><figure class="featured-media"><div class="mediawrapper"><iframe src="https://www.democracynow.org/embed/story/2020/4/17/nyc_nurse_sean_petty_doctors_notes" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe></div></figure></div>
<div class="row">
<div class="columns small-12 medium-4 sidebar-left">
<div class="entry-meta">
<dl class="article__authors byline">
<dt class="meta-label">By </dt>
<dd class="author vcard" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name"><a class="url fn" href="https://truthout.org/authors/amy-goodman/" itemprop="url" rel="author">Amy Goodman</a></span>, </dd>
<dd class="source org" itemprop="sourceOrganization" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization"><span itemprop="name"><a href='https://www.democracynow.org/2020/4/17/nyc_nurse_sean_petty_doctors_notes' itemprop='url'>Democracy Now!</a></span></dd>
</dl>
<dl class="dateline">
<dt class="meta-label">
Published
</dt>
<dd>
<time class="published updated meta-data" datetime="2020-04-17T16:08:42+00:00" itemprop="datePublished dateCreated" content="2020-04-17T16:08:42+00:00">April 17, 2020</time>
</dd>
</dl>
</div>
<div class="meta-label">
Share
</div>
<div class="to4-social">
<div class="to4-social__btns">
<a class="to4-social__btn to4-social__fb" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftruthout.org%2Fvideo%2Fnyc-medical-workers-protest-new-policy-demanding-doctors-notes-for-ill-staffers%2F%3Futm_campaign%3DTruthout%2BShare%2BButtons" target="_top" rel="nofollow">
<span class="to4-social__title show-for-sr">Share via Facebook</span>
<i class="to4-social__icon fab fa-facebook-f"></i>
</a>
<a class="to4-social__btn to4-social__tw" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=NYC%20Medical%20Workers%20Protest%20New%20Policy%20Demanding%20Doctor%E2%80%99s%20Notes%20for%20Ill%20Staffers&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftruthout.org%2Fvideo%2Fnyc-medical-workers-protest-new-policy-demanding-doctors-notes-for-ill-staffers%2F%3Futm_campaign%3DTruthout%2BShare%2BButtons&via=truthout" target="_top" rel="nofollow">
<span class="to4-social__title show-for-sr">Share via Twitter</span>
<i class="to4-social__icon fab fa-twitter"></i>
</a>
<a class="to4-social__btn to4-social__em" href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#" target="_top" rel="nofollow">
<span class="to4-social__title show-for-sr">Share via Email</span>
<i class="to4-social__icon fas fa-envelope"></i>
</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<div class="story_summary">
<div class="text">
<p>A new policy at New York City&rsquo;s public hospitals requires medical workers who call in sick to produce a doctor&rsquo;s note. &ldquo;We know that people just need a mental health day,&rdquo; says Sean Petty, a registered nurse at a public hospital in the Bronx who is organizing a protest against the policy. &ldquo;Thousands of us have been exposed. Health workers are the least tested group of people in this city.&rdquo; Petty is a member of the board of directors of the New York State Nurses Association.</p>
<p><em>Please check back later for full transcript.</em></p>
</div>
</div>
